e":"Hadith on Caliphs: Uhud trembles for Abu Bakr, Umar, and Uthman","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 30, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was climbing Mount Uhud with Abu Bakr, Umar, and Uthman when it began to quake because of them. The Prophet said, \u201cBe still, Uhud! It is but a Prophet, a truthful man, and two martyrs upon you!\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17683,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/21\/umar-apostasy-riddah-murtad\/","url_meta":{"origin":37139,"position":1},"title":"Umar on Apostasy: I did not command it, I was not pleased","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 21, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn al-Qari reported: A man came to Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, from Abu Musa al-Ashari. Umar asked him about the people and he informed him. Then, Umar said, \u201cDo you have any recent news?\u201d Abu Musa said, \u201cYes, a man turned back to unbelief\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24330,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/02\/01\/umar-ikhlaas-allah-take-care\/","url_meta":{"origin":37139,"position":2},"title":"Umar on Sincerity: Allah takes care of those who are sincere","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amir al-Sha\u2019bi reported: Umar ibn Al-Khattab wrote to Abu Musa, may Allah be pleased with them both, saying, \u201cWhoever purifies his intention, Allah will take care of his affairs between people. Whoever embellishes for people what Allah knows is not in his heart, Allah Almighty will disgrace him.\u201d Source: H\u0323ilyat\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33889,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/07\/umar-talaq-triple-divorce\/","url_meta":{"origin":37139,"position":3},"title":"Umar on Talaq: The Caliph punishes men who triple divorce","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 7, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: Whenever a man was brought to Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, who had divorced his wife three times in one sitting, he would flog his back. Source: Sharh\u0323 Ma\u02bba\u0304ni\u0304 al-\u0100tha\u0304r 4488 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Ibn Hajar \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33723,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/10\/13\/umar-on-hamd-how-are-you-all-praise-is-due-to-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":37139,"position":4},"title":"Umar on Hamd: How are you? All praise is due to Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: A man greeted Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, with peace and Umar returned his greeting. Then, Umar said to the man, \u201cHow are you?\u201d The man said, \u201cI praise Allah to you.\u201d Umar said, \u201cThis praise is what I wanted from you.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35185,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/02\/09\/sahaba-qiraah\/","url_meta":{"origin":37139,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Tilawah: Companions recite Quran pleasantly to each other","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 9, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said to Abu Musa while he was sitting in a gathering, \u201cRemind us of our Lord.\u201d Abu Musa would recite to him in a melodious tone as he sat in the gathering. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 7196 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37139","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/d